EZCODE QUOTE END-->On the face of this, this attacks Shintou's character, not his argument.  It says he's &quot;intolerant&quot; (and implies that he's &quot;racist&quot;), or that he's characterized by &quot;intolerance&quot;.  This is a rhetorical device designed to deflect attention away from the actual issues involved and appeal to peoples' emotions.  After all, everyone disagrees with intolerance and racism.  It commits two logical errors, the first being ad hominem attack, and the second being an unfair emotional appeal.<br><br>Unwilling to let this go, however, a few days later, on 01/17/01, in a thread started by yourself, you wrote:<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessage?topicID=248.topic">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...=248.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>     Ranting on and on simply because you [Shintou] know that there are people on the server who don't follow your ideals is not a reasonable way to act...it's <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   sociopathic.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (emphasis mine)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This is just a personal attack, again.  It adds nothing substantial to the argument, and it attacks Shintou's character, not his argument.  It implies that he's got a psychological problem, and that's why he disagrees with you.  It's also an attempt to position yourself above Shintou: &quot;I'm normal, Shintou's sociopathic.&quot;<br><br>Oh, and I can find more, if you like.  Shall I continue?<br><br>Lasgalen <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 1/28/02 4:20:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  